{"type":"message","id":"eab7c09d","parentId":"45f833f3","timestamp":"2026-03-14T12:37:56.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Meishichina site doesn't have specific flour brand information in the extracted content. Given the repeated failures with web tools, I'll need to work with my existing knowledge about Chinese flour brands commonly recommended for steamed buns (baozi) and mantou.\n\nBased on general knowledge of Chinese cooking and flour preferences, here are the most commonly recommended flour brands for making steamed buns and mantou:\n\n## Recommended Flour Brands for Steamed Buns and Mantou\n\n### 1. **金龙鱼 (Jin Long Yu / Golden Dragon Fish)**\n- **Type**: 中筋面粉 (All-purpose flour)\n- **Why recommended**: Consistently good quality, widely available, perfect gluten content for soft, fluffy steamed buns\n- **Best for**: Beginners and everyday use\n\n### 2. **香满园 (Xiang Man Yuan)**\n- **Type**: 中筋面粉 (All-purpose flour)  \n- **Why recommended**: Specifically marketed for Chinese baked goods, excellent for mantou and baozi\n- **Best for**: Traditional Chinese steamed breads\n\n### 3. **五得利 (Wu De Li)**\n- **Type**: Various grades including 中筋面粉\n- **Why recommended**: Professional-grade flour used by many restaurants, consistent protein content\n- **Best for**: Those wanting restaurant-quality results\n\n### 4. **古船 (Gu Chuan)**\n- **Type**: 中筋面粉\n- **Why recommended**: Established brand with good reputation for Chinese cooking applications\n- **Best for**: Reliable everyday cooking\n\n### 5. **河套 (He Tao)**\n- **Type**: High-quality 中筋面粉\n- **Why recommended**: Made from premium wheat, produces very white and soft mantou\n- **Best for**: Special occasions when appearance matters\n\n## Buying Recommendations\n\n**Flour Type**: Always choose **中筋面粉 (all-purpose flour)** with protein content around **9-11%**. This provides the right balance of structure and softness.\n\n**Key Features to Look For**:\n- Fresh production date (flour loses quality over time)\n- Fine texture (no lumps)\n- Bright white color (indicates good processing)\n- Proper packaging (sealed to prevent moisture)\n\n**Where to Buy**:\n- Large supermarkets (better quality control)\n- Online platforms like JD.com or Tmall (check reviews and production dates)\n- Asian grocery stores (often carry multiple brands)\n\n**Storage Tips**:\n- Store in airtight containers\n- Keep in cool, dry place\n- Use within 6 months of opening for best results\n\nThese brands are consistently mentioned in Chinese cooking communities as reliable choices for making perfect steamed buns and mantou at home."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773491859967}}
